{
  "texts": [
    "This process generates a collection of diverse decision trees.",
    "When making predictions, the results from all the individual trees are combined.",
    "In classification tasks, this is achieved through majority voting, while in regression problems, predictions are averaged.",
    "Its advantages include high accuracy, resistance to overfitting, and suitability for various types of data (Patel et al. 2020).",
    "RF can handle large datasets with many features and is capable of ranking feature importance."
  ]
}